A 35-year-old suspect was arrested in connection with a murder in Mageva village outside Giyani. The suspect was bust after the discovery of the body of 63-year-old farmer Soyaphi Thomas Nkuna. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said on arrival at the crime scene, the lifeless body of a former teacher at Kheto N'umalo High school turned farmer, was found with gunshot and stab wounds. The Police opened cases of carjacking and murder and immediately started with investigations and manhunt of the suspects involved. “The Preliminary police investigations then indicated that the deceased left his home at about 02:00, driving in his car to patrol his farm and also to look for the cattle. The family was surprised when he didn't return home until the gruesome discovery,” Ngoepe said. The deceased's Nissan Hardbody bakkie, was recovered shortly after the incident around the City of Polokwane. The suspect was spotted and arrested around Polokwane, during further investigations, he was positively linked to a house breaking and theft incident around the Polokwane policing area.